snippet.textDisplay: There's nothing wrong with Lark that's not wrong with anyone else. It's all in  how we perceive betrayal, heartbreak and downfalls. We all hurt and can become embarrassed over numerous bad things that transpires throughout life. However, it is all in how we process it. For her to have been a big star and perhaps "fall off" can be devastating which can cause major bouts of depression for years to come. Being wealthy and then becoming broke overnight and shunned by those that are supposed be there for you when you fall and not kick you when down, can really really hurt deep inside. I know this 1st hand. However,  my advice to her would be only God can judge you and you are born alone and you shall die alone in this cruel world we all share. Don't worry yourself with how others perceive and treat you anymore. You are still gorgeous and you only need God. Believe in God and God alone. Have faith in him and know that all things are meant to be, rather good or bad. God works in mysterious ways. Sometimes he'll let you fall off to rid you of those around you that prey on you and use you. Once they're gone from your life he'll restore you to who you truly are. A blessed and true child of God. ❤

snippet.textDisplay:
Lark, you will be fine. I wish they would have included you. Maybe down the road with respect of your character in "Saved By The Bell" the Producers will include you in a few episodes.

Mental Illness is a challenge and misunderstood on so many levels. You can't tell me that Hollywood itself is not a world of many struggles including mental illness.

My Mom was a Nurse with Bi-Polar..Many Doctors and Professionals battle with the Illness.

The right thing to do. Mr or Ms Producer. Is to not dismiss Lark but to help her on her journey of recovering. By including in the reboot. A character based off of Larks real illness, her struggles and include in the script. A possible segment..showing Lark desperately tying to hide her illness. But, with the help of her friends. Lark is able to be free of the stigma of mental illness.

Each character that's returning to the show will be Adults. You truly need to shine a light on each of their lives, with laughter, truthfulness and the meaning of everlasting friendships.

snippet.textDisplay:
My heart just aches for Lark. I'm 39 years old, I watched every episode of Saved by the Bell from its debut pilot episode. I loved Lisa Turtle. I still have a great deal of respect, compassion, and empathy for Lark Voorhies, the woman herself. Seeing her trying to get out a simple thought genuinely breaks my heart. It's like she's constantly searching for a better word to use to articulate her thought but once she finds that word, it almost seems like she's lost the point she was trying to get across in the first place. She just ends up saying words that have no cohesiveness with which to bind those words together AS a complete thought. My goodness it's exhausting trying to put what I just watched into words, I can only imagine what it's like living in her mind. I'm glad her mamma has stuck by her all this time and has really tried to help her. I understand why she did what she did. It was in a way to protect her so ppl would stop assuming she was on drugs and would understand it is an illness... But at that time, mental illness wasn't yet something we talked about, unfortunately.
I really hope SBTB reaches out to her and extends an olive branch to be a part of the reboot, she at LEAST deserves to be included as she was one of the leading characters. I don't really want to see it if she's not included to be honest!
